model_explanation: the focus in S1 is on ELLEN. This means that Sam gave grapes to Ellen and no one else. Therefore, it is entailed that Sam didn’t give grapes to Tom, as Tom is not Ellen.
the focus in S1 is on ELLEN. This means Sam gave apples to Ellen and no one else. S2 says Sam didn’t give Ellen apples, which directly contradicts S1.
the focus in S1 is on ROB. This means Sam gave grapes only to Rob and no one else. S2 says Sam also gave grapes to Ellen, which contradicts the claim that Rob is the only recipient of grapes.
the focus in S1 is on ROB. This means Sam gave apples only to Rob and no one else. S2 says Sam also gave apples to Ellen, which contradicts the exclusivity established by S1.
the focus in S1 is on ELLEN. This means Sam gave apples to Ellen and no one else. It is entailed that Sam didn’t give apples to Bill, since Bill is not Ellen.
the focus in S1 is on ROB. This means Sam gave apples to Rob and no one else. Therefore, Sam didn’t give apples to Sue, which is entailed by S1.

the focus in S1 is on ROB. This means Sam gave oranges only to Rob and no one else. S2 talks about apples, so it’s independent. There is no contradiction or entailment because the items (oranges vs. apples) differ.
the focus in S1 is on ROB. This means Sam gave apples only to Rob and no one else. S2 introduces a different fruit (grapes) and doesn’t change the exclusivity of apples, so it’s independent.
the focus in S1 is on ROB. This means Sam gave bananas only to Rob and no one else. Therefore, it is entailed that Sam didn’t give bananas to Ellen, as she is not Rob.

the focus in S1 is on MARY. This means Sam gave apples only to Mary and no one else. S2 introduces Ellen, which contradicts the exclusivity, making it independent here because it breaks that condition.
